Additional Information
For additional information on how we process information in specific countries, please see
here
.
Additional Information
In addition to the details of processing set out in the Policy, additional information relevant to the data processing of Frasers Property Group in specific jurisdictions may be found here.
1.
European (GDPR) Addendum
Safeguards.
Whenever your data is transferred outside the European Economic Area, we ensure that the third-party recipient of the Personal Data is located on a territory that has been recognised by the European Commission as adequate. In the absence of such recognition, we will only transfer your Personal Data outside the European Economic Area when on the basis of valid mechanisms that are expressly recognised in the applicable data protection laws. For example, we may enter into Standard Contractual Clauses as approved by the European Commission (or enter into Binding Corporate Rules) with recipients to protect your personal data in a manner that is consistent with European laws.
2.
South Korea Addendum
Disclosure of personal data to other data controllers.
With your explicit consent, we may disclose your personal data to other data controllers including but not limited to organisations within the Frasers Property Group, owners of the properties on behalf of whom we manage or operate the hotels and/or service apartments, or third parties with whom we conduct joint marketing and cross promotions. You can find the list of the data controllers with whom we share your personal data
here
.
Disclosure of personal data to data processors.
We may also disclose your personal data to data processors whom we engage to undertake certain processing of your personal data under a written contract. You can find the list of the data processors with whom we share your personal data
here
.
3.
China Addendum
Minors.
For the purposes of para 10 of the Policy, we will regard you as a child or minor if you are under 14 years of age.
Personal data provided by others.
Where we obtain your personal data from third party sources, we will process your personal data within the scope of consent you have given to the third party unless otherwise permitted by law or if we have obtained fresh consent from you.
Safeguards.
Where your personal data collected or generated within China is transferred to a country or region outside of China, your personal data will be secured by appropriate safeguards as set forth under Chinese laws and regulations, including without limitation, by the use of the standard contract (where applicable) to be officially published by the Chinese supervisory authority for the transfer of personal data from China to other jurisdictions. To the extent required under applicable law, we will inform you of the relevant information about the transfer and obtain separate consent from you before the transfer of your personal data.
Your Rights.
If you are a close relative of a deceased individual, you may, for your own legitimate rights and interests, contact us in accordance with paragraph 33 of our Policy to exercise the right to access, copy, correct and delete the relevant personal data of the deceased.
4.
Australia Addendum
‘Personal Data’
should be read as ‘personal information’ as defined in the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) (Privacy Act).
Safeguards.
Whenever your personal information is transferred outside Australia, we will:
ensure that the third-party recipient of the personal information is located in a territory that has laws or binding rules that protect the personal information in a way that, overall, is at least substantially similar to the way in which the Australian Privacy Principles at Schedule 1 to the Privacy Act protects such personal information and there are mechanisms available to you to enforce such laws or binding rules; and/or
take reasonable steps to ensure the overseas recipient does not breach the Australian Privacy Principles.
Privacy Complaints.
If you have a complaint about our compliance with the Australian Privacy Principles or in relation to how we deal with a request to access or correct your personal information, you may contact us using the details in Part I “Contacting Us” above. We will use reasonable efforts to respond to your complaint within a reasonable time. If we are unable to satisfactorily resolve your privacy concerns, you can contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner on their website
www.oaic.gov.au
.
5.
Thailand Addendum
Minors.
For the purposes of para 10 of the Policy, we will regard you as a child or minor if you are under 20 years of age. If you wish to use or access our services, you must read this Policy with your parent or legal guardian and you represent that, where required under the applicable laws, you have obtained consent from your parent or legal guardian to provide us with your personal data for the purposes described in this Policy and you will provide evidence of such consent to us when requested.
Your Rights.
In addition to the rights specified under paragraph 26, you are also entitled to the following rights:
Access:
you may request the disclosure of the acquisition of your personal data without your consent.
Erasure:
you may ask us to de-identify your personal data.
Suspension:
you may ask us to suspend the processing of certain personal data about you.
Contacting Us.
If you have any feedback or issues in relation to your personal data, or about the Policy, or wish to make a complaint to us, you may contact the applicable Data Protection Officer at
th.fpt.dpo@frasersproperty.com
.
